cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CE, cs.DB, cs.HC 

This paper proposes a data-driven approach for learning compatibility between organ donors and recipients using electronic health records. The approach involves clustering the feature space and constructing different predictive models for each cluster to capture the heterogeneity of donor and recipient traits. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also involves constructing predictive models, which suggests that it could belong to the computational engineering (cs.CE) and database (cs.DB) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves using electronic health records, which suggests that it could belong to the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
